<section class="recruiter-faq" id="faq">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="section-header reveal">
            <span class="eyebrow">FAQ</span>
            <h2 class="section-title">Quick answers to the questions I get every week.</h2>
            <p class="section-lead">If your hiring manager has a sharper one, send it &mdash; you'll have the answer before your next stand-up.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="recruiter-faq__list reveal">
            <details class="recruiter-faq__item">
                <summary>What's your typical day rate / package range?</summary>
                <div class="recruiter-faq__answer">
                    <p>I keep ranges off the public page on purpose &mdash; banding depends on scope, sector, contract structure (B2B vs PAYE vs perm), and IR35/equivalent treatment. Send the brief and I'll come back with a number that fits. Reply &lt; 24 h.</p>
                </div>
            </details>
            <details class="recruiter-faq__item">
                <summary>Notice period and earliest start?</summary>
                <div class="recruiter-faq__answer">
                    <p>Booking the next 12&ndash;18-month mandate now. Exact start depends on the current engagement; 2&ndash;6 weeks is realistic for most contract roles. Get the JD across and I'll confirm the date in the same reply.</p>
                </div>
            </details>
            <details class="recruiter-faq__item">
                <summary>IR35 / contract structure?</summary>
                <div class="recruiter-faq__answer">
                    <p>Standard B2B via <strong>InnovateIT Kft</strong> (Hungary). Inside-IR35 PAYE umbrella also workable for UK roles. Permanent if it can be structured to match the scope. EU citizen &mdash; no sponsorship needed.</p>
                </div>
            </details>
            <details class="recruiter-faq__item">
                <summary>Is this a real "Head of AI" candidate or a BA who saw the news?</summary>
                <div class="recruiter-faq__answer">
                    <p>Daily production AI in regulated work, not pilots. SWIFT shipped <strong>60% documentation-time savings</strong> using AI-assisted source-code &amp; API analysis. EU AI Act and ISO/IEC 42001 are baseline knowledge. Process mining (Celonis, SAP Signavio) underneath. Read the <a href="/recruiters/#different" data-cta-location="recruiters_faq_diff_link">differentiator block</a>, then the CV.</p>
                </div>
            </details>
            <details class="recruiter-faq__item">
                <summary>On-site requirements?</summary>
                <div class="recruiter-faq__answer">
                    <p>100% remote primary. Up to ~4 travel days per month for kick-offs, audits, and stakeholder workshops. Anything beyond that is a no &mdash; the family base is in Belgium.</p>
                </div>
            </details>
            <details class="recruiter-faq__item">
                <summary>Languages and working time-zones?</summary>
                <div class="recruiter-faq__answer">
                    <p>English (full professional), German (intermediate), Hungarian (native). EU/UK working hours primary; US Eastern Time compatible.</p>
                </div>
            </details>
            <details class="recruiter-faq__item">
                <summary>Can you bring references on the first call?</summary>
                <div class="recruiter-faq__answer">
                    <p>15+ recommendations are public on <a href="{{ site.contact.linkedin }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" data-cta-location="recruiters_faq_linkedin">LinkedIn</a> &mdash; from line managers, peers, and clients across SWIFT, NTT, BT, T-Systems. Direct phone references on request after the intro call.</p>
                </div>
            </details>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

